Chapter 2: Background and Related Work

This chapter provides a comprehensive review of the research domains that underpin this thesis: symbolic regression and equation discovery, evolutionary algorithms for scientific discovery, physics‑guided AI, formal grammars for physical laws, and multi‑objective optimization theory. The review culminates in a gap analysis that motivates our purely evolutionary, provably convergent architecture.

